OL,3,CRemembering Shildon Works 40 years
OL,4,Csince devastating closure
OL,6,FAt its height, the works employed
OL,7,Fnearly 3,000 people but it closed in
OL,8,F1984 - ending 151 years of production.
OL,10,FNearly 2,700 people lost their jobs,
OL,11,Fdevastating the town.
OL,13,FJohn Tomlin, 97, was just 14 when he
OL,14,Fstarted working there, following in
OL,15,Fthe footsteps of his grandfather - who
OL,16,Fwas chief clerk and has a street in
OL,17,FShildon named after him - father and
OL,18,Funcles.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/8
