OL,6,F"I started on the 10 February 1941,"
OL,7,Fhe said. "I was 14 and a half. My
OL,8,Ffather was foreman electrician. It was
OL,9,Fa place where family worked.
OL,11,F"It was a big part of my life. It was
OL,12,Fa big part of everybody's life here."
OL,14,FDulcie Stobbs also worked there, like
OL,15,Fher mother, who was one of the women
OL,16,Fdrafted in to replace men who had gone
OL,17,Fto fight in the Second World War.
OL,19,F"My sister and me put our names down
OL,20,Fand we joined there," she said. "I was
OL,21,Fonly 16.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/8
