OL,6,F"Oh, I liked it. There were some good
OL,7,Fmen there, you know, and I never heard
OL,8,Fany bad language. And that's how I met
OL,9,Fmy boyfriend, my husband."
OL,11,FFellow former worker Dennis Parker
OL,12,Fadded: "I was about the last one to
OL,13,Fcome out of Shildon Works.
OL,15,F"We were like one big family."
OL,17,FRail wagons were built in Shildon from
OL,18,F1833. It meant for the first time,
OL,19,Fhuge quantities of coal mined in
OL,20,Fnearby pits could be transported more
OL,21,Fquickly than ever.
