OL,3,CRemembering Shildon Works 40 years
OL,4,Csince devastating closure
OL,6,F"It was an enormous contribution to
OL,7,FBritain's economic success. It was
OL,8,Fvery much the motorway, the artery of
OL,9,FBritish industry."
OL,11,FHe added: "So it had this very long
OL,12,Flifetime but things started to change.
OL,13,FIt was very much how the economy was
OL,14,Fchanging towards a more road transport-
OL,15,Fbased economy. Railways were quite
OL,16,Fcumbersome. Sending goods by rail was
OL,17,Flabour intensive."
OL,19,FDemand fell and in 1984 the works
OL,20,Fclosed, despite it still making a
OL,21,Fprofit at the time.
