OL,3,CRemembering Shildon Works 40 years
OL,4,Csince devastating closure
OL,6,FForty years later, people in Shildon
OL,7,Fstill feel its loss.
OL,9,FOne former worker told ITV Tyne Tees:
OL,10,F"Everything that was made in the works
OL,11,Fwas spent in the town, money-wise. So
OL,12,Fthe only things you've got now are
OL,13,Ftakeaways. There's very few shops."
OL,15,F"My grandfather, my dad, my uncle, my
OL,16,Fbrother, my son, we all worked for the
OL,17,Fworks," said another. "And when it
OL,18,Fclosed it was heartbreaking. It was, I
OL,19,Fremember my mum, my son crying on the
OL,20,Fdoorstep.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G7/8
